<br>
<p>The black bar between the query and the template alignment shows the column score with
<b>|</b>, <b>+</b>, <b>.</b>, <b>-</b>, <b>=</b>
indicating scores from '<i>very good</i>' to '<i>very bad</i>'.
<aside style="font-size:8pt;">(Please see the <a href="#" style="font-size:8pt" title="HHpred help on results" onclick="openHelpWindow('help_results');">Results</a> page for a more detailed explanation).</aside>

<br><br>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px">
<p>The colored histogram bars show the proportion of the most abundant amino acids in the corresponding
column of the underlying MSA. One has to keep in mind that HHpred relies on HMM-HMM comparison and that 
both query and template HMMs are derived from an alignment of homologs.<br> 
As an example, the first column from the query alignment contains approximately 40% serine (S) and 20% alanine (A). 
Residues that are less frequent, i.e. below 10% each, are not shown. 
That is why badly conserved columns, which contain a lot of residues, with proportions
of less than 10%, have a low total height, whereas well conserved columns assume the maximum height. 
The residues are colored according to their general physico-chemical properties.</p></div><br>
<div style="float:right; width:200px; margin-left:20px; margin-top: -25px;">
<table>
<tr>
        <th><b>Color Scheme</b></th>
    </tr>
