<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>

<p>The histogram view is beneficial in that it allows to grasp the character of similarity between two profile HMMs that HHpred
has detected. In a single glance, one can often tell apart false positives, which occur due to a similar amino
acid composition, from real homologs with their conserved motifs. Functional motifs or structurally important
amino acids can be quickly spotted and high conservation of the involved residues is expected.
</p>

